1
00:00:21,731 --> 00:00:24,358
I needed to die so that you could live.

2
00:00:24,442 --> 00:00:26,026
I gave myself to Ace...

3
00:00:26,110 --> 00:00:27,111
They were the ones who bailed me out?

4
00:00:27,194 --> 00:00:29,113
Maybe you should ask the Veronas about it.

5
00:00:29,196 --> 00:00:32,616
I know who the masterminds
behind this operation are.

6
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,785
If you had let me fix it
in the first place,

7
00:00:34,869 --> 00:00:35,703
this wouldn't have happened!

8
00:00:35,786 --> 00:00:37,913
You are going to be taking
bigger responsibilities.

9
00:00:37,997 --> 00:00:39,623
<i>You and Gem are not going anywhere.</i>

10
00:00:39,707 --> 00:00:42,209
- I'll just go ahead.
- Are you disrespecting me?

11
00:00:42,293 --> 00:00:43,919
<i>Why would those people</i>
<i>try to go against you,</i>

12
00:00:44,003 --> 00:00:45,129
<i>the ones who actually know the law?</i>

13
00:00:45,212 --> 00:00:46,380
I'm not here to make a scene.

14
00:00:46,464 --> 00:00:47,923
I trust you to handle that reporter.

15
00:00:48,007 --> 00:00:49,550
I think the Veronas will have her killed.

16
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:51,844
<i>Teo, that's why you shouldn't</i>
<i>go against the Veronas.</i>

17
00:00:51,927 --> 00:00:53,429
If you know where your mom is,
please tell me.

18
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:54,597
<i>They're going to kill her.</i>

19
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:56,223
<i>I will bring her home to you, alive.</i>

20
00:00:56,307 --> 00:00:57,600
<i>What else do you know about my mother?</i>

21
00:00:57,683 --> 00:01:00,019
If you don't tell me,
I'll find the answer myself.

22
00:01:01,729 --> 00:01:05,065
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

23
00:01:38,724 --> 00:01:39,975
Hello?

24
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:44,271
How did she escape?

25
00:01:45,231 --> 00:01:46,982
What do you mean you don't know?

26
00:01:47,066 --> 00:01:50,569
Stupid! You didn't even
stay with her to finish the job?

27
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:53,197
Where is she now?

28
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,618
Go and find her.

29
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:09,004
Oh, Gem.

30
00:02:09,088 --> 00:02:10,673
- I'm glad you're here.
Mama.

31
00:02:11,549 --> 00:02:15,427
Gem, I'd like you to meet
Roberto Labradores, our client.

32
00:02:16,178 --> 00:02:19,807
Bert, my daughter-in-law, Gem.

33
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:22,393
- Nice meeting you, Gem.
Nice to meet you.

34
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:24,603
Okay? All right.

35
00:02:24,687 --> 00:02:27,231

I better get going. I'll pay you soon.

36
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:30,609
Just send the receipt
for the down payment to my e-mail.

37
00:02:30,693 --> 00:02:32,820
- Sure. Will do.
Thank you.

38
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,114
Thank you. Thank you.

39
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:38,784

He's a black marketer, Mama.

40
00:02:38,868 --> 00:02:40,953

I don't care what he does,

41
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:45,249
as long as the transaction
between the two of us is legal.

42
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:47,793
Since you're here,
I have something for you to do.

43
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:50,337
What is it, Mama?

44
00:02:51,255 --> 00:02:53,215
There's going to be
a jewelry expo tomorrow,

45
00:02:53,299 --> 00:02:54,550
and I can't attend.

46
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:58,429
So, you are going to go on behalf of me
and represent the company.

47
00:03:00,014 --> 00:03:03,058
Uhm... Ace already knows that
Teo is going to drive you there.

48
00:03:03,142 --> 00:03:05,019
- Larajean.
Yes, Madam.

49
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:08,105
You will accompany Gem
to the jewelry expo tomorrow.

50
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:11,984
And I also have some jewelry
to be delivered to a client there.

51
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:13,652
Yes, ma'am.

52
00:03:13,736 --> 00:03:16,530
Ma'am Gem, I'm happy to assist you.

53
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:22,620
Go for it, bro.

54
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:24,955
Just staring at her
isn't going to do anything.

55
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:28,667
She looks like she's having a rough time.
Maybe she needs someone to talk to.

56
00:03:29,627 --> 00:03:31,795


57
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:43,057
Would you like anything else, ma'am?

58
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:45,601
Are you here to laugh at me, too?

59
00:03:45,684 --> 00:03:47,353
Why would I do that?

60
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:53,484
Everybody is saying
we're human traffickers.

61
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,111
Even if what they're
accusing your parents of is true,

62
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:58,364
I don't believe you're involved in that.

63
00:03:59,198 --> 00:04:00,783
But I feel so bad.

64
00:04:01,784 --> 00:04:03,953

Look at the way they're looking at me.

65
00:04:04,036 --> 00:04:05,871
Ronnie, I'm not a bad person.

66
00:04:05,955 --> 00:04:08,499
I know. You've got an attitude, sure,

67
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,961
- but you're not a bad person.
Wow.

68
00:04:12,044 --> 00:04:14,171
- That's very comforting.
There!

69
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:19,343
That's the Raya I know. A fighter.

70
00:04:20,344 --> 00:04:22,680
Someone who just doesn't
let things get to her.

71
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,765
As long as you know who you are,

72
00:04:24,848 --> 00:04:27,518
and you're not doing anything wrong,
that's all that matters.

73
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:31,772
Well... I feel like
I'm already doing something wrong.

74
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:35,442

All the luxury stuff I flaunt...

75
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:39,780
it's possible it really did come
from the suffering of others.

76
00:04:39,863 --> 00:04:42,825
Raya! Raya!

77
00:04:42,908 --> 00:04:44,576
- Hey.
Hold on.

78
00:04:46,537 --> 00:04:48,872
You have to see this!

79
00:04:48,956 --> 00:04:50,958
They say she's also
the one making those memes

80
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:52,292
that are going viral.

81
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:57,506
- That bitch.

82
00:04:57,589 --> 00:05:00,509
- Wait, wait.
Wait for me! Wait up!

83
00:05:00,592 --> 00:05:04,513


84
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:07,516
- Hey, Raya, you're gonna trip!
Raya, calm down.

85
00:05:07,599 --> 00:05:09,476
- We'll get there.
Raya!

86
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:12,438
- Raya... Raya--
Stop that!

87
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:14,565
You're really not going
to leave me alone, are you?

88
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:17,443
- Don't even bother with her.
Listen to your boyfriend.

89
00:05:17,526 --> 00:05:20,404
Why are you so mad?
What I'm saying is true.

90
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:23,532
You and your family are human traffickers.

91
00:05:23,615 --> 00:05:26,994
You have the nerve to brag
about your luxury things

92
00:05:27,077 --> 00:05:29,371
when they came from illegal stuff.

93
00:05:29,455 --> 00:05:30,664
You're pushing it!

94
00:05:30,748 --> 00:05:31,790
- Raya!
Just one!

95
00:05:31,874 --> 00:05:35,961
Just one slap to shut her up!

96
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:39,757
Forget it. You'll just make things worse.

97
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:42,509
Hey, why are you mad at me?

98
00:05:42,593 --> 00:05:44,219
You should be mad at your parents.

99
00:05:44,303 --> 00:05:46,221
You should take it up with them.

100
00:05:46,764 --> 00:05:48,057
Excuse me, miss.

101
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:49,975
What you are doing is cyberlibel.

102
00:05:50,059 --> 00:05:52,728
Actually, that also counts
as cyberbullying, right?

103
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:53,896
- Yeah.
That's right.

104
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:55,647
She can report you for that.

105
00:05:55,731 --> 00:05:57,191
You're already 18, right?

106
00:05:57,983 --> 00:06:00,277
Perfect! She's old enough to go to jail!

107
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,654
Can you endure seven
or eight years inside?

108
00:06:02,738 --> 00:06:04,531
Six years minimum. Can you endure that?

109
00:06:04,615 --> 00:06:05,824
You two, you wanna join her?

110
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:08,452
You're really pushing it.

111
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:10,245
- Hey! Hey! Hey!
Raya.

112
00:06:10,329 --> 00:06:13,082


113
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:25,886
Raya! Raya, wait!

114
00:06:27,679 --> 00:06:30,808
-
Yeah, I know, right?

115
00:06:36,105 --> 00:06:37,648
Pa, where did you go?

116
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:39,608
Issay said you were out the whole day.

117
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:41,235
You weren't with our neighbors.

118
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:44,029
Don't be mad, okay?

119
00:06:44,113 --> 00:06:47,199
I accepted the job offered by the Veronas.

120
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:48,700
Huh?

121
00:06:48,784 --> 00:06:52,204
Because we need money
to pay for our expenses.

122
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:54,540
But we can pay for them just fine.

123
00:06:56,542 --> 00:06:58,210
You're hiding something from me.

124
00:06:59,336 --> 00:07:01,547
I failed to pay the property tax
while you were away.

125
00:07:02,131 --> 00:07:03,382
How much do we owe?

126
00:07:04,007 --> 00:07:05,175
Two hundred
and twenty thousand pesos.

127
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:07,761
- What?
220,000!

128
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:10,764
So I've made up my mind.

129
00:07:10,848 --> 00:07:12,766
I will accept the job offer,

130
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:15,644
and you can't do anything to stop me.

131
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:20,315


132
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:22,526
Ma? Where are you?

133
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:25,529
I'm fine. I'm safe. How are you?

134
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:28,198
Ma, please come home. I miss you.

135
00:07:28,282 --> 00:07:29,825
I can't, dear.

136
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:33,537
Ma!

137
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,955
- Who are you?
Come with us!

138
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:37,916
-<i> Ma, help!</i>
Jenny? Jenny! Dear?

139
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,917
Jenny!

140
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:40,419
- Get in!
Ma! Help!

141
00:07:40,502 --> 00:07:42,129


142
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:45,257
Hello? Jenny?

143
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:49,553
What? Was she talking to her mother?

144
00:07:51,555 --> 00:07:53,473
"Someone took Jenny, my daughter!"

145
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,810
Teo, pull over and get out.
I'll drive myself.

146
00:07:56,894 --> 00:07:58,562
Just go home and come back tomorrow.

147
00:07:58,645 --> 00:07:59,479
Okay, sir.

148
00:07:59,563 --> 00:08:02,024


149
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,693


150
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:12,075
-
Hello, Eric. Are you done?

151
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:13,452
Where are you?

152
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:15,954
I'll meet you there.

153
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:19,833
<i>Teo!</i>

154
00:08:19,917 --> 00:08:21,335
Teo, they took my daughter!

155
00:08:21,418 --> 00:08:22,336
I know.

156
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:24,171
You know?

157
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:26,465
Are you messing with me?
Are you with them?

158
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:27,841
No.

159
00:08:27,925 --> 00:08:30,177
But they will do everything
to make you do their bidding.

160
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:33,555
If that's what it'll take
to get my daughter back, fine!

161
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:36,266
I'll do what they want!

162
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:39,228
Do you think doing that will
make them spare your daughter?

163
00:08:39,311 --> 00:08:41,897
<i>Daniela, don't go anywhere.</i>
<i>Stay there. I'll come find you.</i>

164
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:43,106
I'll take care of this.

165
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:45,901
You'll see your daughter again.

166
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:54,451
Ma! Ma, help me!

167
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,494
Hey! Give me that!

168
00:08:55,577 --> 00:08:56,995
You animals!

169
00:08:57,079 --> 00:08:58,997
If you want to see your daughter alive...

170
00:08:59,081 --> 00:09:00,999
- Ma, help!
- ...come find her!

171
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:03,210
- Where did you take her?
- <i>Santa Mesa.</i>

172
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:06,296
- <i>Ma!</i>
- <i>Kapayapaan Street. Number 31.</i>

173
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,464
Help me, Mama!

174
00:09:21,603 --> 00:09:22,813
Daniela?

175
00:09:31,697 --> 00:09:34,157
- Hello?
- I know where the Veronas

176
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:36,285
are hiding their
human trafficking victims.

177
00:09:36,994 --> 00:09:38,078
I found their hideout.

178
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:39,496
Who is this?

179
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:46,837
Go inside your rooms.

180
00:09:47,462 --> 00:09:48,463
Move it.

181
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:02,978
Hey, you.

182
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:05,063
Get out. Hurry!

183
00:10:05,814 --> 00:10:06,982
Come here.

184
00:10:09,318 --> 00:10:10,444
- Ma!
- Dear!

185
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:14,156
- Ma, help me!
- Dear...

186
00:10:14,239 --> 00:10:15,699
Take her inside.

187
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:18,869
Get in. Move.

188
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:29,463
What are you waiting for?
Open up the gates!

189
00:10:29,546 --> 00:10:32,007
Wait, Edwin went to take a piss.
He's got the keys.

190
00:10:34,134 --> 00:10:35,260
Edwin!

191
00:10:37,596 --> 00:10:38,722
Edwin!

192
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:02,621
Unload all the boxes
from the truck

193
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:04,790
and bring them to the warehouse.

194
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:13,340
Hold on.

195
00:12:01,555 --> 00:12:04,141
"Where are you guys?"

196
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:30,500
Yes?

197
00:12:34,171 --> 00:12:35,297
What?

198
00:12:43,013 --> 00:12:44,764
- Sir?
- Move all of them

199
00:12:44,848 --> 00:12:46,391
to the compound in Palacios. Do it now.

200
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:47,601
Yes, sir.

201
00:12:47,684 --> 00:12:48,518
Let's go.

202
00:12:50,645 --> 00:12:52,189
Men, ready to move!

203
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,106
We're moving.

204
00:12:57,569 --> 00:12:59,946
Come on! We're moving! Pack your things!

205
00:13:13,001 --> 00:13:15,212
Hurry up! Go down!

206
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:25,180
- What the...
- Hurry up and get it!

207
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:28,141
- Hey!
- Hey!

208
00:13:28,225 --> 00:13:30,185
Jenny!

209
00:13:31,895 --> 00:13:32,854
Ma, wake up!

210
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:45,700
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Who are you?

211
00:13:45,784 --> 00:13:46,868
- Let's go!
- Dear, just go!

212
00:13:46,952 --> 00:13:49,538
Help my mom!

213
00:13:49,621 --> 00:13:50,956
- Ma!
- Let's go!

214
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:52,958
Ma, please no! Ma, wake up!

215
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,543
Ma! Ma, wake up!

216
00:13:54,626 --> 00:13:56,419
- Help her!
- Let's go! Let's go!

217
00:13:59,172 --> 00:14:00,632
Men, move!

218
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,721
I need my mom! Ma!

219
00:14:08,974 --> 00:14:09,933
My mom!

220
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:12,060
- You need to help my mom!
- Let's go!

221
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:13,853
Please stop!

222
00:14:13,937 --> 00:14:15,480
Ma!

223
00:14:15,564 --> 00:14:16,565
Let me go!

224
00:14:18,817 --> 00:14:20,569
Tuguegarao!

225
00:14:20,652 --> 00:14:22,654
Teo, here's your ticket.

226
00:14:24,948 --> 00:14:27,242
I'm sorry about this, Jepoy.
I didn't know who else to call.

227
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:28,326
Don't sweat it.

228
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:30,495
Jenny, I've talked to your aunt.

229
00:14:30,579 --> 00:14:32,664
She's going to pick you up
at the terminal in Tuguegarao.

230
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:35,041
Teo, I bought two tickets.

231
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:36,042
Aren't you going to go with her?

232
00:14:36,126 --> 00:14:37,460
If only I could.

233
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:39,254
You know I'm on thin ice.

234
00:14:39,838 --> 00:14:41,756
- I can go with her.
- Are you sure?

235
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:45,135
She was kidnapped, and her mom
died in front of her.

236
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:47,721
- I can't let her travel alone.
- Okay.

237
00:14:48,430 --> 00:14:49,806
Thank you, Jepoy.

238
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,266
I'll make it up to you.

239
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:53,143
I haven't forgotten what I promised.

240
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:54,561
Don't worry about it.

241
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:55,854
I'll look after Jenny.

242
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:58,148
Jenny, study hard, okay?

243
00:15:00,191 --> 00:15:02,444
Don't tell anyone about what happened.

244
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:05,030
Don't trust anyone. They might find you.

245
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:06,531
Don't worry.

246
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:09,200
I will seek justice
for your mother's death.

247
00:15:09,284 --> 00:15:10,160
Tuguegarao! Tuguegarao!

248
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:11,703
Quail eggs, corn.

249
00:15:14,748 --> 00:15:16,249
Go on.

250
00:15:17,459 --> 00:15:19,336
Jepoy, take care of her. Keep me posted.

251
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:20,378
Take care.

252
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,464
- Let's go, Jenny.
- Take care, guys.

253
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:25,759
Tuguegarao! Tuguegarao!

254
00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:30,180
Tuguegarao!

255
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:38,855
Pa, I didn't know Teo fell asleep here.

256
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,523
He just got home.

257
00:15:42,108 --> 00:15:43,693
Teo, son.

258
00:15:44,486 --> 00:15:45,612
Hey, wake up.

259
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:50,909
- Pa.
- Where have you been?

260
00:15:50,992 --> 00:15:52,827
At the police station.

261
00:15:53,495 --> 00:15:54,829
I went to visit Jenny.

262
00:15:54,913 --> 00:15:56,373
Is she okay?

263
00:15:56,915 --> 00:15:58,249
Yes.

264
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:00,877
But she can't visit here for now.

265
00:16:01,544 --> 00:16:03,004
Why, Teo?

266
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,257
Don't worry, you'll see each other again

267
00:16:07,342 --> 00:16:09,511
once her kidnappers are caught.

268
00:16:12,305 --> 00:16:14,182
<i>The authorities now have in custody</i>

269
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:16,976
<i>seventeen people who were supposed to be</i>

270
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:18,645
<i>illegally flown out of the country.</i>

271
00:16:18,728 --> 00:16:22,232
<i>Two members of the group</i>
<i>were killed in the encounter.</i>

272
00:16:22,941 --> 00:16:26,528
<i>And one of those who was found dead</i>
<i>before the police arrived</i>

273
00:16:26,611 --> 00:16:28,613
<i>was the whistleblower, Daniela Ordoñez.</i>

274
00:16:28,697 --> 00:16:30,448
Oh, my gosh!

275
00:16:30,532 --> 00:16:32,701
What are people going to say?

276
00:16:33,284 --> 00:16:36,955
That woman's been
pinning us down for a long time!

277
00:16:37,038 --> 00:16:40,792
Most likely, that loudmouthed reporter
will corner us again!

278
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:42,502
And it's not just that.

279
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:46,172
It's hard to recover the losses
we incurred overnight.

280
00:16:46,256 --> 00:16:47,507
I will fix this.

281
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:49,134
No, you won't!

282
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:52,971
I already anticipated these problems.

283
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:54,806
Yes, the property is mine.

284
00:16:54,889 --> 00:16:56,141
I won't deny that.

285
00:16:56,224 --> 00:16:58,685
But that warehouse
is just being rented from me.

286
00:16:58,768 --> 00:17:00,228
Who is renting from you, Attorney?

287
00:17:05,984 --> 00:17:07,360
Where is this person?

288
00:17:07,444 --> 00:17:09,154
He's based in Qatar,

289
00:17:09,237 --> 00:17:12,073
but since the raid,
I haven't been able to contact him.

290
00:17:12,157 --> 00:17:14,534
It seems like that demon
has gone into hiding as well.

291
00:17:14,617 --> 00:17:17,078
But you can't deny that
you used to be a legal attaché

292
00:17:17,162 --> 00:17:18,621
in Morocco and Dubai.

293
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,791
There's a possibility
you still have connections there.

294
00:17:22,709 --> 00:17:23,960
We also received a tip

295
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:26,045
that the victims
were allegedly taken there.

296
00:17:26,129 --> 00:17:28,548
I also read your official statement.

297
00:17:28,631 --> 00:17:32,802
One of those who died
was Daniela Ordoñez, wasn't she?

298
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:34,804
And she admitted she was a recruiter.

299
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:36,514
She had all the motive in the world

300
00:17:36,598 --> 00:17:40,518
to name whoever was necessary
to protect her real handlers.

301
00:17:40,602 --> 00:17:43,104
And as for you, son,

302
00:17:43,188 --> 00:17:46,900
maybe next time,
when you're ready to do this.

303
00:17:46,983 --> 00:17:48,651
But for now,

304
00:17:48,735 --> 00:17:50,612
he still has a lot to learn.

305
00:18:02,165 --> 00:18:04,834
Look, I'm open
to a full investigation.

306
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:09,005
But you know that
Judge Verona is also my friend, right?

307
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:11,883
And now that he's being cornered,
I'm being dragged into this as well.

308
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:15,804
Why don't you look at this
from another angle?

309
00:18:15,887 --> 00:18:18,807
Who stands to benefit
if his name is tarnished,

310
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:20,683
if both of us are implicated?

311
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:23,520
Because what you have
is circumstantial evidence.

312
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:26,523
Inferences, assumptions,
and a dying statement

313
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:28,525
from a compromised witness.

314
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:32,737
There's no direct link,

315
00:18:32,821 --> 00:18:35,657
no probable cause
that can stand up in court.

316
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:42,121
Oh, at last,
we're finally vindicated.

317
00:18:42,205 --> 00:18:45,416
The nerve of that Daniela Ordoñez.

318
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,627
She even covered up for her boss,

319
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:51,464
who was, in fact,
the real human trafficker.

320
00:18:51,548 --> 00:18:53,049
She even dragged us into it.

321
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,969
I mean, why would she do that, Ma?

322
00:18:56,052 --> 00:18:57,804
But of course...

323
00:18:57,887 --> 00:19:00,723
so that the real mastermind
can go scot-free.

324
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:02,976
I had better look into this.

325
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:05,854
We'll coordinate with the police
to find this person.

326
00:19:05,937 --> 00:19:07,146
He's not alone, Pa.

327
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:09,858
We need to find all of them,
including their accomplices.

328
00:19:10,525 --> 00:19:12,151
Everyone who wants to destroy us.

329
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:14,404
Well, I hope they all get caught, love.

330
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:17,490
Those human traffickers don't have souls.

331
00:19:17,574 --> 00:19:19,868
Can you imagine turning
your fellow human beings

332
00:19:19,951 --> 00:19:21,119
into a business?

333
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:24,163
As if they're just objects to be sold.

334
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:27,709
That's the worst thing
you can do to someone else.

335
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:31,254
They're not human, they're monsters.

336
00:19:31,337 --> 00:19:33,131
You're right, Gem.

337
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:38,136
I hope all of them will rot in jail.

338
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:42,724
Well, at least now we can
go back to our normal lives.

339
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:47,562
Gem, are you ready
for the expo you're attending today?

340
00:19:47,645 --> 00:19:49,981
- Of course, Mama.
- Hmm.

341
00:19:53,818 --> 00:19:58,489
Ma'am, if you only knew,
I'm so honored to assist you.

342
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:02,076
And thank you as well
for the overnight stay at the hotel.

343
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:04,954
Larajean, this is work, not a vacation.

344
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:06,414
Yes, ma'am. I know.

345
00:20:06,497 --> 00:20:09,792
And I'll really, really work hard, ma'am.

346
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:12,837
I'm already expecting
that this event will be successful.

347
00:20:12,921 --> 00:20:14,881
It's just that...

348
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:20,553
won't we be affected
by the accusations against your family?

349
00:20:20,637 --> 00:20:25,183
We might get tomatoes
or eggs thrown at us, ma'am.

350
00:20:25,266 --> 00:20:27,101
It would be better
if they were diamonds.

351
00:20:27,602 --> 00:20:29,729
Well then, that's your challenge.

352
00:20:29,812 --> 00:20:32,357
Let's see if you can sell
in this kind of environment.

353
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,693
Okay, ma'am. I'm up for it.
Challenge accepted.

354
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,238
Hey, Teo, you're so quiet.

355
00:20:39,822 --> 00:20:41,157
You should be excited.

356
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,826
You'll just drop us off,
then you'll have a staycation there.

357
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:46,704
Jean, I'll just keep an eye on you there.

358
00:20:46,788 --> 00:20:48,831
Wow! Me too?

359
00:20:49,332 --> 00:20:51,960
That's so sweet of you.

360
00:20:56,673 --> 00:20:57,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

361
00:20:57,924 --> 00:20:58,967
Enjoy your stay.

362
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,597
Ah, ma'am, here's your keycard.

363
00:21:04,681 --> 00:21:05,890
Sixth floor.

364
00:21:05,974 --> 00:21:08,059
Okay.
But I'll just go to my room first.

365
00:21:08,142 --> 00:21:09,143
I'll just freshen up.

366
00:21:09,227 --> 00:21:10,728
- Bring this to the expo.
- Yes, ma'am.

367
00:21:10,812 --> 00:21:12,438
Larajean, don't leave that behind, okay?

368
00:21:12,522 --> 00:21:14,983
Yes, ma'am.
Let me help you with your luggage.

369
00:21:15,066 --> 00:21:16,401
I can manage.

370
00:21:16,484 --> 00:21:18,486
Or if you want,
you can also check your room.

371
00:21:19,237 --> 00:21:21,280
We only have one room, ma'am?

372
00:21:22,323 --> 00:21:24,075
No. I'll be in the dorm-type room.

373
00:21:24,158 --> 00:21:26,160
I'll be with the other drivers.

374
00:21:54,731 --> 00:21:56,649
Hey, have you been waiting?

375
00:21:56,733 --> 00:22:00,153
I actually fell asleep. I'm hungry now.

376
00:22:00,695 --> 00:22:01,988
We did a lot of detours.

377
00:22:02,989 --> 00:22:04,991
And someone's guarding me.

378
00:22:05,992 --> 00:22:07,243
Your husband?

379
00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:09,037
No.

380
00:22:09,787 --> 00:22:10,747
It's Teo.

381
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:17,545
And his ex-girlfriend
who sucks up to Ace's mom.

382
00:22:17,628 --> 00:22:20,757
- Can we start now?
- Oh, yeah, I forgot.

383
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:38,399
What do you think?

384
00:22:38,483 --> 00:22:39,734
Do I look okay?

385
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:43,279
Wow!

386
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:45,865
You're amazing.

387
00:22:46,783 --> 00:22:48,451
And handsome!

388
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:51,621
You never lose your touch,
do you, Chameleon?

389
00:22:54,874 --> 00:22:56,918
It's been a long time
since someone called me that.

390
00:22:57,001 --> 00:22:58,836
- Do you like it?
- No.

391
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:01,547
Come on. Let's start.

392
00:23:04,425 --> 00:23:07,470
- Come on.
- Ah.

393
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:10,681
You look handsome.

394
00:23:13,601 --> 00:23:15,228
- Is it done?
- Come see.

395
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,313
You're incredible.

396
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,273
You're fawning over my looks again.

397
00:23:19,357 --> 00:23:20,817
When will the passport be released?

398
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,401
Next week.

399
00:23:22,485 --> 00:23:24,987
But if you want to get it earlier,

400
00:23:25,071 --> 00:23:26,906
- just add--
- Doesn't matter how much,

401
00:23:26,989 --> 00:23:28,991
as long as I get it as soon as possible.

402
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:43,673
Gem, we have to talk.

403
00:23:44,799 --> 00:23:47,176
- What's with you?
- You have to leave.

404
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:51,222
The Veronas are murderers. They're demons.

405
00:23:51,305 --> 00:23:55,101
Everything Daniela Ordoñez said
about the Veronas is all true.

406
00:23:55,184 --> 00:23:57,145
The human trafficking? All of it is true.

407
00:23:57,228 --> 00:23:58,896
You escaped a syndicate,

408
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:00,648
- but now you're back in one.
- What's this about, Teo?

409
00:24:01,149 --> 00:24:02,900
Huh? Is this about your mother?

410
00:24:05,486 --> 00:24:06,654
Huh?

411
00:24:06,737 --> 00:24:09,615
What are you really up to?
Did you talk with Daniela?

412
00:24:09,699 --> 00:24:12,577
That's not important.
What matters now is your escape.

413
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:14,495
You have to cut these people off.

414
00:24:15,037 --> 00:24:18,040
- It's not that easy.
- It is. I'll help you.

415
00:24:21,419 --> 00:24:24,088
And I won't stop
until you escape from them.

416
00:24:24,172 --> 00:24:27,008
Can you stop them? Think about yourself.

417
00:24:29,051 --> 00:24:30,469
Don't worry about me.

418
00:24:30,553 --> 00:24:32,972
And don't waste what I did for you.

419
00:24:34,724 --> 00:24:36,475
You think I'd still be here

420
00:24:36,559 --> 00:24:38,686
if I just let them have their way with me?

421
00:24:42,565 --> 00:24:44,483
I can handle myself, Teo.

422
00:24:52,158 --> 00:24:54,660
Hm? Your coffee's gone cold.

423
00:24:58,122 --> 00:24:59,624
Where were you yesterday?

424
00:25:01,042 --> 00:25:03,044
You didn't answer my call.

425
00:25:03,127 --> 00:25:06,380
I went out for a snack,
and I didn't have my phone with me.

426
00:25:06,464 --> 00:25:07,632
I left it in the car.

427
00:25:09,175 --> 00:25:10,551
I've been bored since yesterday.

428
00:25:10,635 --> 00:25:12,845
I just don't understand Ma'am Gem.

429
00:25:12,929 --> 00:25:15,181
It's like I'm talking to a wall.

430
00:25:16,182 --> 00:25:20,144
I'm trying to be friendly
and cooperative...

431
00:25:20,228 --> 00:25:21,562
Let it go.

432
00:25:22,396 --> 00:25:23,564
Thank you.

433
00:25:24,815 --> 00:25:27,485
I thought you'd never talk to me again.

434
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:29,570
Is it my fault if the people
I asked to help you

435
00:25:29,654 --> 00:25:30,780
didn't answer me?

436
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:34,408
All I know is that you were free,
so I thought that was because of me.

437
00:25:34,492 --> 00:25:37,245
But it's still wrong to claim
something that's not yours.

438
00:25:37,328 --> 00:25:39,038
That's fraud.

439
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:40,748
Still, thank you...

440
00:25:41,958 --> 00:25:43,251
for your efforts.

441
00:25:49,340 --> 00:25:50,800
Teo, there's...

442
00:25:51,634 --> 00:25:52,969
there's something
I've been meaning to ask you

443
00:25:53,052 --> 00:25:54,804
for a long time now.

444
00:25:54,887 --> 00:25:56,472
That...

445
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:59,016
Yana from Morocco...

446
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:01,185
do you love her?

447
00:26:02,019 --> 00:26:03,229
That was ages ago.

448
00:26:04,814 --> 00:26:06,482
I've erased that from my mind.

449
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:10,569
But back then,
did you know right away that...

450
00:26:11,362 --> 00:26:12,655
it was going to be her?

451
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,868
Hey! What's your answer?

452
00:26:18,619 --> 00:26:20,496
Where do your questions even come from?

453
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:21,664
From Ma'am Gem!

454
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:25,543
We talked about, well, us.

455
00:26:25,626 --> 00:26:27,211
And Yana.

456
00:26:27,295 --> 00:26:29,338
But you didn't know about Yana before.

457
00:26:29,422 --> 00:26:31,424
- Exactly!
- It's done, Larajean.

458
00:26:31,966 --> 00:26:34,218
I have a lot more to deal with than that.

459
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:38,931
But if ever you're ready to get into

460
00:26:39,015 --> 00:26:41,434
- a relationship again--
- No.

461
00:26:42,184 --> 00:26:43,144
I have no plans.

462
00:26:44,395 --> 00:26:45,479
Not anymore.

463
00:26:45,563 --> 00:26:47,440
What about your bloodline?

464
00:26:47,523 --> 00:26:51,777
Still! If you ever change your mind...

465
00:26:54,238 --> 00:26:55,448
I'm ready.

466
00:26:56,157 --> 00:27:00,286
I know it's completely wrong
that I cheated on you.

467
00:27:01,162 --> 00:27:02,705
It's only you, Teo.

468
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:06,250
It's a shame, the time
we spent together, if...

469
00:27:07,001 --> 00:27:09,962
It would be a bigger shame
to ruin a new family

470
00:27:10,046 --> 00:27:13,382
when I'm not ready,
instead of fixing my own.

471
00:27:15,301 --> 00:27:17,178
There are other men
out there, Larajean.

472
00:27:18,220 --> 00:27:19,263
Not me.

473
00:27:21,474 --> 00:27:23,893
It's only you.

474
00:27:23,976 --> 00:27:25,936
Whoever's destined for you
will come along.

475
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:26,896
And that's not me.

476
00:27:26,979 --> 00:27:28,356
It can only be you!

477
00:27:32,151 --> 00:27:35,071
Anyway, do you know
who helped you back then?

478
00:27:37,406 --> 00:27:39,158
Well, you have a point.

479
00:27:39,241 --> 00:27:41,911
It's over. What matters now is...

480
00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:44,121
the present.

481
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:48,334
You know, Miss Gem
is really stressing me out.

482
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:51,879
I've texted her a lot
but she's not replying.

483
00:27:54,215 --> 00:27:57,843
Gem... is now really the right time?

484
00:27:58,511 --> 00:27:59,720
I have no idea.

485
00:28:02,139 --> 00:28:04,266
I'm just worried about Teo and his father.

486
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:06,894
Gem, this is not about them.

487
00:28:06,977 --> 00:28:08,896
I'm talking about our departure.

488
00:28:09,814 --> 00:28:11,649
Won't the Veronas be able to find us?

489
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:14,860
They don't control the whole world.

490
00:28:18,489 --> 00:28:19,824
Besides...

491
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:23,577
we can't leave as long as
they're with the Veronas.

492
00:28:23,661 --> 00:28:26,997
You know, I can't understand you.
You're putting yourself in danger.

493
00:28:27,081 --> 00:28:29,208
Can't we just leave?

494
00:28:44,348 --> 00:28:46,851
- What a gentleman.
- Not really.

495
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:50,521
Okay, I'll make sure everything
is good before you leave.

496
00:28:51,188 --> 00:28:52,940
Hey, be careful.

497
00:28:53,441 --> 00:28:55,734
Of course, you too.

498
00:28:55,818 --> 00:28:56,735
Take care.

499
00:28:56,819 --> 00:28:58,612
Why? Did I lose an ear?

500
00:29:04,493 --> 00:29:05,744
Just be careful.

501
00:29:05,828 --> 00:29:07,538
Yes, I promise.

502
00:29:07,621 --> 00:29:09,415
I will treat you to a good meal.

503
00:29:09,915 --> 00:29:13,544
We just need to do a good job.

504
00:29:22,136 --> 00:29:23,137
Hello?

505
00:29:23,220 --> 00:29:24,680
Hello, Madam Katarina?

506
00:29:26,182 --> 00:29:30,311
Um, I don't know how to say this, but...

507
00:29:30,394 --> 00:29:33,147
I believe you must know.

508
00:30:27,409 --> 00:30:28,619
Love.

509
00:30:32,706 --> 00:30:34,208
Love, what's the problem?

510
00:30:58,315 --> 00:30:59,692
Do you want to talk?

511
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:04,029
What's the problem?

512
00:31:12,037 --> 00:31:13,914
- Do you have another man?
- What?

513
00:31:16,542 --> 00:31:18,961
Who did you let inside your room?

514
00:31:19,044 --> 00:31:21,505
Ace, I don't know
what you're talking about.

515
00:31:24,633 --> 00:31:26,552
Ace!

516
00:31:26,635 --> 00:31:28,304
Are you cheating on me?

517
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:31,932
Who are you cheating on me with?

518
00:31:32,725 --> 00:31:34,143
Don't lie to me!

519
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:35,060
Who is he?

520
00:31:35,144 --> 00:31:37,938
I'm not cheating on you with another man!

521
00:31:45,321 --> 00:31:46,780
What's going on there?

522
00:31:46,864 --> 00:31:48,866
Ma, what's happening?

523
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:50,242
They're fighting!

524
00:31:50,326 --> 00:31:51,869
- Ace! Ace!
- Brother!

525
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:54,038
Ace, open the door!

526
00:31:54,121 --> 00:31:56,248
Ma, what's happening?

527
00:31:56,332 --> 00:31:57,750
- Help!
- Gem!

528
00:31:57,833 --> 00:31:58,876
- Pa!
- Ace!

529
00:31:58,959 --> 00:32:00,836
- Pa!
- Steven, get the key!

530
00:32:02,296 --> 00:32:04,048
- Open up!
- Ace!

531
00:32:04,131 --> 00:32:06,634
- Ace!
- Steven!

532
00:32:06,717 --> 00:32:09,803
Ace, what's going on?

533
00:32:09,887 --> 00:32:11,472
Who the hell did you meet?

534
00:32:11,555 --> 00:32:13,098
Ace, open the door!

535
00:32:13,182 --> 00:32:15,726
Ace!

536
00:32:15,809 --> 00:32:17,019
Ace!

537
00:32:18,228 --> 00:32:20,147
Oh, my gosh!

538
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:22,566
Ace! Ace.

539
00:32:23,233 --> 00:32:24,818
Ace, what happened?

540
00:32:24,902 --> 00:32:26,612
Gem! Gem!

541
00:32:27,696 --> 00:32:29,323
Steven, get the car ready!

542
00:32:34,536 --> 00:32:36,413
Are you going to file a case against Ace?

543
00:32:36,914 --> 00:32:38,165
I should.

544
00:32:39,583 --> 00:32:41,043
But I won't.

545
00:32:45,047 --> 00:32:48,133
Thank you, Gem.
But I also want to be fair.

546
00:32:48,217 --> 00:32:49,968
I need those photos.

547
00:32:50,052 --> 00:32:51,428
For the medical-legal report.

548
00:32:52,096 --> 00:32:53,472
Evidence.

549
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:55,683
I'll use it to prevent Ace...

550
00:32:56,517 --> 00:32:58,227
from hurting you any further.

551
00:32:58,310 --> 00:33:00,312
He shouldn't have done this.

552
00:33:02,314 --> 00:33:03,315
But is it true?

553
00:33:04,233 --> 00:33:05,943
Is there someone else?

554
00:33:06,026 --> 00:33:08,153
Are you having an affair?

555
00:33:09,613 --> 00:33:10,906
No, Papa.

556
00:33:11,824 --> 00:33:13,617
That man...

557
00:33:14,159 --> 00:33:16,453
He was a client who was also at the expo.

558
00:33:18,038 --> 00:33:21,875
He just wanted to see the jewelry with me.

559
00:33:21,959 --> 00:33:23,877
He's harmless.

560
00:33:23,961 --> 00:33:25,879
He's gay, Papa.

561
00:33:26,964 --> 00:33:29,007
You know
my son gets jealous easily.

562
00:33:30,426 --> 00:33:32,886
You should've practiced discernment, Gem.

563
00:33:32,970 --> 00:33:34,138
I know.

564
00:33:35,305 --> 00:33:37,933
But I didn't think that...

565
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:40,352
he would think I would do that.

566
00:33:41,854 --> 00:33:44,064
Is Ace having me followed?

567
00:33:44,148 --> 00:33:45,399
I don't know.

568
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:47,693
But I'm asking you,

569
00:33:47,776 --> 00:33:50,404
let's resolve this privately.

570
00:33:51,989 --> 00:33:53,073
As a family.

571
00:34:01,331 --> 00:34:03,250
The next time, Larajean...

572
00:34:03,751 --> 00:34:06,044
you have to be more careful.

573
00:34:07,087 --> 00:34:08,547
Context is key.

574
00:34:08,630 --> 00:34:13,051
I don't know why
I thought Ma'am Gem was having an affair.

575
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:15,679
Did you really think?

576
00:34:16,638 --> 00:34:17,639
Did you?

577
00:34:18,348 --> 00:34:19,308
Yes.

578
00:34:19,391 --> 00:34:23,312
I really thought she had a lover,

579
00:34:23,395 --> 00:34:26,023
so I acted impulsively.

580
00:34:26,106 --> 00:34:30,319
I just get really upset
about things like that

581
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:32,321
because of what happened to my family.

582
00:34:33,614 --> 00:34:36,450
I don't want to see
any relationship destroyed

583
00:34:36,533 --> 00:34:38,452
because of cheating.

584
00:34:40,162 --> 00:34:41,538
You know, Larajean,

585
00:34:42,915 --> 00:34:45,626
true loyalty is rare in this family.

586
00:34:45,709 --> 00:34:48,837
People become loyal
when it's convenient.

587
00:34:48,921 --> 00:34:53,550
But the moment you saw
and you felt that something was off,

588
00:34:53,634 --> 00:34:55,677
you immediately told me,

589
00:34:55,761 --> 00:34:57,554
and you showed me what you saw.

590
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:00,933
That makes it different.

591
00:35:01,016 --> 00:35:03,894
And regardless of the very messy outcome,

592
00:35:03,977 --> 00:35:05,687
you actually impressed me.

593
00:35:06,188 --> 00:35:07,856
Hopefully, this won't be the last time.

594
00:35:09,650 --> 00:35:10,859
Sit down.

595
00:35:14,363 --> 00:35:15,781
I said sit down.

596
00:35:27,668 --> 00:35:29,336
You know what this is, right?

597
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:31,004
A blue sapphire.

598
00:35:32,381 --> 00:35:36,635
But do you know what this stone
stands for and what it symbolizes?

599
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:43,600
The sapphire symbolizes loyalty.

600
00:35:44,351 --> 00:35:49,064
I want you to have this ring
to symbolize your loyalty to me

601
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:50,691
and to remind you

602
00:35:51,483 --> 00:35:56,864
that I reward people who are loyal to me.

603
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:04,162
Put it on.

604
00:36:08,834 --> 00:36:09,793
There.

605
00:36:09,877 --> 00:36:12,629
So every time you see that ring,

606
00:36:12,713 --> 00:36:16,049
it will remind you of your loyalty to me

607
00:36:16,133 --> 00:36:17,676
and most of all,

608
00:36:18,594 --> 00:36:19,928
that the Veronas...

609
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:24,182
never forget.

610
00:36:39,907 --> 00:36:40,991
Larajean.

611
00:36:42,451 --> 00:36:43,702
Did something happen to Ma'am Gem?

612
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:45,537
Yeah.

613
00:36:45,621 --> 00:36:49,416
I heard she got hurt by Sir Ace
because she was with a man.

614
00:36:49,499 --> 00:36:51,501
Weren't you with her last night?

615
00:36:51,585 --> 00:36:52,878
Did you see anyone with her?

616
00:36:53,503 --> 00:36:55,881
No! I was sent home early

617
00:36:55,964 --> 00:37:00,385
because she said she was meeting
someone at the hotel café.

618
00:37:01,136 --> 00:37:04,389
Ah. So you knew she was meeting someone.

619
00:37:06,016 --> 00:37:08,143
I don't like your tone.

620
00:37:09,102 --> 00:37:12,022
Don't start with your "hero act"
for Ma'am Gem again.

621
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:14,232
Why are you getting worked up?

622
00:37:14,316 --> 00:37:15,901
Because you're implying things.

623
00:37:16,401 --> 00:37:19,154
So what if I knew she was meeting someone?

624
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:22,407
How about you?
Didn't you pick her up that night?

625
00:37:22,491 --> 00:37:24,826
Maybe you're the one who saw
who she was with.

626
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:26,244
I didn't pick her up.

627
00:37:28,622 --> 00:37:29,623
Teo.

628
00:37:30,582 --> 00:37:32,292
I know you're kind to everyone.

629
00:37:32,793 --> 00:37:34,503
But your concern for Miss Gem?

630
00:37:35,003 --> 00:37:38,799
The way you're willing
to fight me for her?

631
00:37:39,341 --> 00:37:42,844
I don't know. It's making me jealous.

632
00:37:47,432 --> 00:37:49,518
Teo, what happened to us?

633
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:55,107
Is this still about
what happened in Morocco?

634
00:37:57,901 --> 00:37:59,820
Because I had a boyfriend there?

635
00:38:00,362 --> 00:38:01,655
I know I...

636
00:38:02,322 --> 00:38:04,616
deserve your anger, yes.

637
00:38:05,367 --> 00:38:08,036
But why are you treating me
like I killed someone?

638
00:38:12,582 --> 00:38:14,626
Teo, I'm not Yana.

639
00:38:16,128 --> 00:38:18,797
I'm not the one who deceived you
and put you in danger,

640
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,716
so can you not treat me this way?

641
00:38:21,717 --> 00:38:23,385
You're right.

642
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:28,140
I'm sorry for the way I've acted.

643
00:38:30,267 --> 00:38:33,103
At the end of the day,
we're still childhood friends.

644
00:38:34,521 --> 00:38:36,064
We grew up together.

645
00:38:37,149 --> 00:38:38,775
We once shared dreams together.

646
00:38:42,154 --> 00:38:43,488
And fell in love.

647
00:38:46,158 --> 00:38:48,744
Let's just forget about
all the bad things that happened.

648
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:51,038
Let's start over.

649
00:39:11,058 --> 00:39:12,976
I saw Gem earlier.

650
00:39:13,685 --> 00:39:15,103
I know she'll get better soon,

651
00:39:15,187 --> 00:39:17,064
but why does she have to
get hurt like that?

652
00:39:17,856 --> 00:39:19,608
- Raya--
- No, Ma!

653
00:39:20,734 --> 00:39:23,403
Ace, you love her, right?

654
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:27,282
But what you did?
That's not love.

655
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:30,660
It's more nuanced than that, Raya.
You wouldn't understand.

656
00:39:30,744 --> 00:39:33,830
Raya, your brother has issues, okay?

657
00:39:33,914 --> 00:39:35,290
And we're trying to fix it.

658
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:39,419
We're addressing it...
so he won't do that again.

659
00:39:39,503 --> 00:39:40,879
- But Ma--
- Raya.

660
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:43,006
It was just a misunderstanding.

661
00:39:43,090 --> 00:39:44,424
Let's just move on.

662
00:39:46,885 --> 00:39:48,261
Can I serve you salmon?

663
00:39:49,012 --> 00:39:50,180
Yes, please.

664
00:39:52,474 --> 00:39:53,558
Hello, Pa?

665
00:39:53,642 --> 00:39:55,727
Someone from City Hall
was looking for you.

666
00:39:55,811 --> 00:39:59,272
They left you a document
that you must see right away.

667
00:39:59,356 --> 00:40:01,149
Just leave it on my desk.

668
00:40:01,233 --> 00:40:02,859
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

669
00:40:02,943 --> 00:40:03,985
It states here

670
00:40:04,069 --> 00:40:06,655
that this is your last notice
before our house is seized.

671
00:40:07,155 --> 00:40:08,698
Last notice before our house is seized?

672
00:40:08,782 --> 00:40:10,033
Yes, Pa.

673
00:40:11,368 --> 00:40:12,786
This is bad.

674
00:40:13,453 --> 00:40:15,539
All right. I'll take care of it.

675
00:40:15,622 --> 00:40:17,541
Are you sure, Pa?

676
00:40:17,624 --> 00:40:20,001
Yes, I'll take care of it, okay?

677
00:40:20,085 --> 00:40:21,336
I'll hang up now.

678
00:40:24,756 --> 00:40:26,508
- Alonzo.
- Oh, Judge.

679
00:40:29,636 --> 00:40:32,222
I heard your conversation.
Is your house going to be seized?

680
00:40:32,305 --> 00:40:33,557
Yes, sir.

681
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:37,102
Well, Judge, it's all my fault.

682
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:40,522
I had to settle a debt...

683
00:40:41,231 --> 00:40:44,651
so I put off paying
our house's property tax.

684
00:40:44,734 --> 00:40:48,989
Now, it's piled up
to a couple hundred thousand.

685
00:40:49,573 --> 00:40:53,869
I've borrowed some money to pay it off,
but it's still not enough.

686
00:40:55,370 --> 00:40:57,289
Judge, maybe...

687
00:40:59,416 --> 00:41:00,667
maybe you can help me.

688
00:41:00,750 --> 00:41:03,170
I'll work for it, sir.

689
00:41:03,253 --> 00:41:06,756
If you want,
you can deduct it from my salary

690
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:09,968
so I can pay it little by little.

691
00:41:10,051 --> 00:41:13,471
I'm not asking for charity.
I'm going to work for it, sir.

692
00:41:13,555 --> 00:41:14,890
Okay.

693
00:41:15,932 --> 00:41:17,517
Let's talk about this with Teo.

694
00:41:17,601 --> 00:41:19,269
Judge, um...

695
00:41:19,936 --> 00:41:22,731
can we not let Teo know about this?

696
00:41:23,231 --> 00:41:24,566
Let's just keep it between us,

697
00:41:24,649 --> 00:41:26,776
because my son already
has a lot on his plate.

698
00:41:29,988 --> 00:41:33,033
When I saw that video, I felt so defeated,

699
00:41:35,911 --> 00:41:38,079
So betrayed.

700
00:41:40,665 --> 00:41:43,335
I can't believe the woman
that I've loved all my life...

701
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:44,961
could ever do that to me.

702
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:49,966
I did nothing but love her.

703
00:41:54,221 --> 00:41:55,472
How can she do that to me?

704
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:57,557
I just wish I acted differently.

705
00:41:58,099 --> 00:41:59,935
But she deserves it.

706
00:42:00,018 --> 00:42:01,770
What's your plan now, sir?

707
00:42:01,853 --> 00:42:05,273
All I know is I ended up hurting her…

708
00:42:05,357 --> 00:42:06,900
because I was hurting, too.

709
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:11,863
And I wouldn't be hurting like this
if I didn't love her.

710
00:42:14,241 --> 00:42:16,159
I just want her to learn her lesson.

711
00:42:17,953 --> 00:42:19,162
But...

712
00:42:20,205 --> 00:42:21,790
I also don't want to lose her...

713
00:42:49,693 --> 00:42:50,986
Hi, love.

714
00:42:57,450 --> 00:42:58,576
Oh, what?

715
00:43:00,036 --> 00:43:03,707
The way you're looking at me...
I'm not a monster.

716
00:43:05,166 --> 00:43:08,878
It's still me, your husband,
the love of your life.

717
00:43:09,504 --> 00:43:10,839
Nothing has changed, right?

718
00:43:13,008 --> 00:43:14,384
So, is this how it is now, Gem?

719
00:43:16,094 --> 00:43:17,095
Now I'm the bad guy,

720
00:43:17,178 --> 00:43:20,724
but you're the victim, just because
you're in the hospital.

721
00:43:20,807 --> 00:43:23,435
Well, you know,
if you had just remained faithful,

722
00:43:23,518 --> 00:43:24,602
I wouldn't have hurt you.

723
00:43:24,686 --> 00:43:26,438
But this is your fault.

724
00:43:26,521 --> 00:43:27,814
You're the one
who did something.

725
00:43:29,357 --> 00:43:30,817
Love, come on, just tell me.

726
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:32,527
Just tell me who it was.

727
00:43:33,069 --> 00:43:35,030
If you confess, I'll forgive you...

728
00:43:36,448 --> 00:43:38,992
and we can both start over
like nothing ever happened.

729
00:43:39,075 --> 00:43:41,369
Gem, I love you. You know that.

730
00:43:44,372 --> 00:43:46,041
Fuck!

731
00:43:46,124 --> 00:43:48,251
Fuck! Shit!

732
00:43:48,335 --> 00:43:49,586
Why'd you do that?

733
00:43:49,669 --> 00:43:52,047
Ow!

734
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,592
- Get him out of here!
- Sir, what happened?

735
00:43:55,675 --> 00:43:56,843
- She stabbed me!
- Get him out!

736
00:43:56,926 --> 00:43:59,846
- Sir, please step outside.
- No! No, no! That's my wife!

737
00:43:59,929 --> 00:44:01,014
- Gem!
- Sir, please step outside.

738
00:44:01,097 --> 00:44:02,057
- Please!
- Gem, we can fix this!

739
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:04,809
- Please listen to me!
- Sir! Sir!

740
00:44:04,893 --> 00:44:06,686
Sir, please leave!

741
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:07,979
Gem, come on! That's my wife!

742
00:44:28,708 --> 00:44:29,709
Hey, man.

743
00:44:31,836 --> 00:44:34,422
What is wrong with you? Huh?

744
00:44:56,694 --> 00:44:58,947
Hey! What's going on?

745
00:45:00,240 --> 00:45:01,616
Stop!

746
00:45:05,954 --> 00:45:08,915
Buddy, I need a stretcher here
in the parking lot.

747
00:45:08,998 --> 00:45:09,999
Sir?

748
00:45:11,835 --> 00:45:13,169
Sir?

749
00:45:17,048 --> 00:45:18,675
- Hey.
- Hm?

750
00:45:19,634 --> 00:45:21,052
- Sir?
- What is that?

751
00:45:21,136 --> 00:45:23,555
Uh... just practice.

752
00:45:23,638 --> 00:45:25,140
It's been a long time coming.

753
00:45:26,266 --> 00:45:27,892
What are you doing here? It's late.

754
00:45:27,976 --> 00:45:31,062
I just wanted to borrow, uh,
a charger from Issay.

755
00:45:31,146 --> 00:45:33,606
But I think she's already asleep.
I'll come back tomorrow.

756
00:45:33,690 --> 00:45:35,066
- Okay. See you.
- Bye.

757
00:45:39,237 --> 00:45:41,322
- Where's my son?
- Ma'am. Sir.

758
00:45:42,574 --> 00:45:45,326
My son. My son...

759
00:45:46,494 --> 00:45:47,704
My gosh.

760
00:45:48,246 --> 00:45:50,832
Do you remember the face
of the person who did this to you?

761
00:45:54,210 --> 00:45:56,588
Doc, how is my son?

762
00:45:56,671 --> 00:46:01,634
Ma'am, we already ran the X-rays,
and he has a fractured rib and arm.

763
00:46:01,718 --> 00:46:04,345
But the good thing is
there's no internal bleeding.

764
00:46:04,429 --> 00:46:06,389
So nothing life-threatening.

765
00:46:07,098 --> 00:46:10,768
Based on our investigation,
none of his things are missing.

766
00:46:10,852 --> 00:46:12,520
His phone and wallet
were not taken.

767
00:46:12,604 --> 00:46:14,230
Robbery is ruled out, Judge.

768
00:46:14,314 --> 00:46:16,566
No one saw who did this to my son?

769
00:46:16,649 --> 00:46:18,943
I'm the only guard in the area, sir.

770
00:46:19,027 --> 00:46:22,906
I heard a noise,
so I went to where your son was.

771
00:46:22,989 --> 00:46:24,491
What about the CCTV footage?

772
00:46:24,574 --> 00:46:26,910
Not even a single passerby?

773
00:46:26,993 --> 00:46:29,412
The CCTV camera is broken.

774
00:46:29,496 --> 00:46:30,747
It looks like it was done intentionally.

775
00:46:31,247 --> 00:46:33,041
I cannot accept that reason.

776
00:46:33,124 --> 00:46:35,502
I will sue this hospital for negligence.

777
00:46:35,585 --> 00:46:37,212
Excuse us.

778
00:46:37,295 --> 00:46:38,630
Sir.

779
00:46:43,343 --> 00:46:45,345
He's so swollen.

780
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:03,780
What are you doing here?

781
00:47:13,957 --> 00:47:15,625
Why did you do that to Ace?

782
00:47:16,334 --> 00:47:18,002
What if someone saw you?

783
00:47:18,086 --> 00:47:20,046
What if he recognized you?

784
00:47:20,129 --> 00:47:21,756
I made sure no one did.

785
00:47:24,717 --> 00:47:26,135
Gem.

786
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:30,348
Why are you putting up with him?

787
00:47:31,724 --> 00:47:33,268
Do you love him?

788
00:47:34,269 --> 00:47:36,354
Do you love yourself?

789
00:47:36,437 --> 00:47:38,231
He's going to kill you.

790
00:47:38,314 --> 00:47:39,857
I already told you...

791
00:47:40,817 --> 00:47:42,694
My situation is complicated.

792
00:47:42,777 --> 00:47:44,362
It's easy, Gem.

793
00:47:44,445 --> 00:47:46,239
You're the one complicating it.

794
00:47:46,906 --> 00:47:48,533
Leave him.

795
00:47:49,784 --> 00:47:51,119
Why can't you leave?

796
00:47:51,953 --> 00:47:53,788
What? Is it money?

797
00:47:54,914 --> 00:47:56,708
Where's the money you stole in Morocco?

798
00:47:56,791 --> 00:47:59,127
You can use that to start again.

799
00:47:59,919 --> 00:48:01,588
I already told you, Teo.

800
00:48:01,671 --> 00:48:03,381
I'm not leaving him.

801
00:48:03,464 --> 00:48:05,008
It's my decision.

802
00:48:06,217 --> 00:48:08,553
I don't have anything to explain to you.

803
00:48:12,098 --> 00:48:13,725
You know, it'd be better...

804
00:48:16,019 --> 00:48:17,562
if you'd just leave.

805
00:48:28,406 --> 00:48:30,450
Don't move! Give me your belongings!

806
00:48:30,533 --> 00:48:32,452
<i>Don't move! Give me your belongings!</i>

807
00:48:33,661 --> 00:48:35,830
Hello, Teo! Want some snacks?

808
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:37,707
- Later. Thank you.
- Okay.

809
00:48:39,876 --> 00:48:41,127
Pa.

810
00:48:42,420 --> 00:48:44,422
I was able to pay the real estate tax.

811
00:48:44,505 --> 00:48:46,341
Here's the receipt.

812
00:48:46,424 --> 00:48:49,344
- Where did you get the money?
- From my friend.

813
00:48:49,427 --> 00:48:52,680
He was a mechanic I worked with in Japan.

814
00:48:52,764 --> 00:48:53,931
He's well-off now.

815
00:48:54,474 --> 00:48:55,642
He let you borrow money so easily?

816
00:48:55,725 --> 00:48:57,852
Yes, we're like...

817
00:48:57,935 --> 00:49:00,938
at the time,
Lito and I were like brothers.

818
00:49:01,731 --> 00:49:03,232
Don't worry, son.

819
00:49:03,316 --> 00:49:05,401
I made a promise, didn't I?

820
00:49:05,485 --> 00:49:06,903
I'll pay that back in installments.

821
00:49:06,986 --> 00:49:08,821
Especially now that I have a job.

822
00:49:09,572 --> 00:49:11,783
Okay, Pa. I'll help you pay it off.

823
00:49:11,866 --> 00:49:14,077
Come on, loosen up a bit.

824
00:49:14,661 --> 00:49:16,913
It's because of Ma'am Gem, isn't it?

825
00:49:17,664 --> 00:49:19,374
I just don't understand, Pa.

826
00:49:20,625 --> 00:49:21,709
Why...

827
00:49:22,669 --> 00:49:24,754
can't she leave her husband?

828
00:49:26,047 --> 00:49:27,215
He's going to kill her.

829
00:49:27,298 --> 00:49:28,633
It's her decision.

830
00:49:29,300 --> 00:49:31,135
If she wants to be a masochist

831
00:49:31,219 --> 00:49:34,013
or be her husband's punching bag,
you can't do anything about it.

832
00:49:34,097 --> 00:49:37,558
We don't want Sir Ace
and the judge to know about this.

833
00:49:38,518 --> 00:49:39,477
You might get in trouble.

834
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:54,742
Give us some privacy.

835
00:49:58,705 --> 00:50:01,290
Ma'am, call me if you need anything.

836
00:50:01,999 --> 00:50:03,042
Thanks.

837
00:50:06,379 --> 00:50:08,047
Did you like it?

838
00:50:08,548 --> 00:50:09,966
Is this your peace offering

839
00:50:10,049 --> 00:50:11,467
for all the punches and kicks
I got from you?

840
00:50:11,968 --> 00:50:14,011
You were trying to kill me, remember?

841
00:50:14,846 --> 00:50:16,806
But I know you did it,

842
00:50:17,557 --> 00:50:19,517
so you could freely be
with your other man.

843
00:50:20,977 --> 00:50:23,062
My God, Ace.

844
00:50:23,146 --> 00:50:24,647
I want to meet him.

845
00:50:25,940 --> 00:50:27,400
The client you were talking about.

846
00:50:29,152 --> 00:50:30,611
Can I borrow your phone, please?

847
00:50:31,154 --> 00:50:32,363
Who is he?

848
00:50:40,621 --> 00:50:43,249
Tony Castellano. Call him if you want.

849
00:50:43,833 --> 00:50:45,835
"Tony Castellano."

850
00:50:51,799 --> 00:50:52,842
Thank you.

851
00:51:05,938 --> 00:51:08,566
- Hi, Gem!
- Hi, Mr. Castellano.

852
00:51:09,734 --> 00:51:12,570
I'd like you to meet my husband,
Attorney Ace Verona.

853
00:51:12,653 --> 00:51:14,572
This is Mr. Antonio Castellano.

854
00:51:15,072 --> 00:51:16,407
Hi, Attorney.

855
00:51:17,784 --> 00:51:19,285
Just call me Tony.

856
00:51:19,368 --> 00:51:20,703
Nice meeting you, Tony.

857
00:51:21,704 --> 00:51:23,581
Well, care to join us?

858
00:51:23,664 --> 00:51:25,625
Um, sorry, I'm in a rush.

859
00:51:25,708 --> 00:51:27,293
I can't stay long.

860
00:51:27,376 --> 00:51:28,795
Are you sure
you don't want to have dinner?

861
00:51:28,878 --> 00:51:30,880
Yes, it's okay. Um...

862
00:51:31,631 --> 00:51:36,052
So, what can I do for you,
Gem and Attorney?

863
00:51:36,677 --> 00:51:38,554
You said it was important.

864
00:51:38,638 --> 00:51:41,641
Yes. Well, my husband over here,

865
00:51:41,724 --> 00:51:46,020
he wants to meet, you know,
my very, very loved client, such as you.

866
00:51:46,103 --> 00:51:47,480
So, Tony, tell me.

867
00:51:47,563 --> 00:51:48,856
Is my wife good?

868
00:51:50,358 --> 00:51:52,693
What he means to say
is he appreciates your trust

869
00:51:52,777 --> 00:51:54,904
on our brand, of course.

870
00:51:54,987 --> 00:51:56,405
I appreciate you so much.

871
00:51:56,489 --> 00:51:58,574
And I have one question.

872
00:51:59,158 --> 00:52:00,743
Did he like what you bought?

873
00:52:01,494 --> 00:52:03,246
This?

874
00:52:03,329 --> 00:52:05,414
Of course. He loves it.

875
00:52:05,498 --> 00:52:06,624
- That's good to hear.
- You know,

876
00:52:06,707 --> 00:52:08,709
you never disappoint, diva.

877
00:52:08,793 --> 00:52:10,378
It's very pretty.

878
00:52:12,755 --> 00:52:15,508
- You didn't tell him?
- Well...

879
00:52:16,217 --> 00:52:20,054
Oh, my God. Actually, Attorney,
I have a partner.

880
00:52:20,137 --> 00:52:22,265
Alvin and I have been
together for five years,

881
00:52:22,849 --> 00:52:25,935
and we have been planning
our engagement for a long time.

882
00:52:26,686 --> 00:52:29,397
The ring your wife made.

883
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:31,232
Yes!

884
00:52:31,315 --> 00:52:33,401
- It's beautiful.
- Five years, that's...

885
00:52:33,484 --> 00:52:35,236
- impressive.
- Right?

886
00:52:35,319 --> 00:52:36,904
I didn't say yes easily.

887
00:52:36,988 --> 00:52:38,698
I wanted to savor the feeling
of being beautiful.

888
00:52:38,781 --> 00:52:41,242
- You are beautiful.
- Just like you.

889
00:52:41,325 --> 00:52:43,911
Babe, shall we go?

890
00:52:43,995 --> 00:52:46,664
Oh, I'm sorry, we have a date.
That's why I'm in a rush.

891
00:52:46,747 --> 00:52:48,583
- It's fine, it's fine.
- Babe.

892
00:52:48,666 --> 00:52:51,335
- This is Gem.
- It's a pleasure.

893
00:52:51,419 --> 00:52:52,628
And her husband,

894
00:52:52,712 --> 00:52:54,797
- Attorney Verona.
- Hello.

895
00:52:54,881 --> 00:52:56,716
My partner, Alvin.

896
00:52:57,466 --> 00:52:58,384
Wait, guys.

897
00:52:58,467 --> 00:53:00,845
Sorry, guys, but we'll have to go.

898
00:53:00,928 --> 00:53:02,680
It's fine. Go ahead, enjoy.

899
00:53:02,763 --> 00:53:05,057
- Thank you for this.
- Bye.

900
00:53:05,141 --> 00:53:06,392
- Bye!
- Bye.

901
00:53:12,064 --> 00:53:13,566
I told you.

902
00:53:13,649 --> 00:53:15,860
You clearly saw that
they're very, very much in love.

903
00:53:15,943 --> 00:53:18,237
Why didn't you tell me that Tony was gay?

904
00:53:18,321 --> 00:53:20,072
Would that have made a difference?

905
00:53:20,156 --> 00:53:21,657
I know you, Ace.

906
00:53:21,741 --> 00:53:25,202
You'd want to see him in person
to justify your assaulting me.

907
00:53:25,286 --> 00:53:27,288
Don't you ever pull this on me again.

908
00:53:27,872 --> 00:53:29,999
I hate looking like a fool.

909
00:53:30,791 --> 00:53:32,209
Of course.

910
00:53:40,092 --> 00:53:42,094
Are you really okay now, Ma'am Gem?

911
00:53:42,178 --> 00:53:44,513
Madam Katarina was right.

912
00:53:44,597 --> 00:53:46,682
You really had a bad fall.

913
00:53:47,767 --> 00:53:50,186
Do not patronize me, Larajean.

914
00:53:50,770 --> 00:53:53,522
I know you sent the video to Mama.

915
00:53:54,649 --> 00:53:57,193
What? What video, ma'am?

916
00:53:58,694 --> 00:53:59,946
You're so bad at this.

917
00:54:00,029 --> 00:54:01,739
Your acting sucks.

918
00:54:01,822 --> 00:54:03,908
Ma'am, I really don't...

919
00:54:03,991 --> 00:54:06,202
I don't know anything, ma'am.
It wasn't me.

920
00:54:06,285 --> 00:54:08,537
- Cross my heart and hope to die.
- Really?

921
00:54:15,962 --> 00:54:17,922
Even if you die today?

922
00:54:22,218 --> 00:54:24,971
Ma'am, don't joke around like that.

923
00:54:25,054 --> 00:54:27,098
Who says I'm joking around?

924
00:54:30,559 --> 00:54:34,563
Next time you put me in danger...

925
00:54:37,191 --> 00:54:39,110
Go on, try to hurt me.

926
00:54:39,735 --> 00:54:41,946
I know your real identity.

927
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:44,740
Yana Kassir.

928
00:54:46,659 --> 00:54:48,828
You don't know what I'm capable of.

929
00:54:50,496 --> 00:54:52,123
I didn't come this far

930
00:54:52,206 --> 00:54:54,709
to let someone like you threaten me.

931
00:54:55,584 --> 00:54:57,378
Don't test me.

932
00:54:58,337 --> 00:55:00,589
I'll take you to hell myself.

933
00:55:14,979 --> 00:55:16,981
Confirmed.

934
00:55:17,064 --> 00:55:18,649
Ma'am Gem is Yana.

935
00:55:19,483 --> 00:55:20,443
No.

936
00:55:20,526 --> 00:55:22,361
Didn't I tell you to stop?

937
00:55:22,445 --> 00:55:25,489
She told me herself.
She even threatened me.

938
00:55:25,573 --> 00:55:27,074
I told you to stop.

939
00:55:27,158 --> 00:55:28,534
You already know.

940
00:55:29,285 --> 00:55:31,203
Have you two talked about it?

941
00:55:31,287 --> 00:55:33,956
That you know who she is? That criminal?

942
00:55:34,040 --> 00:55:36,625
I thought you wanted us
to be okay, Larajean?

943
00:55:36,709 --> 00:55:38,085
How?

944
00:55:38,169 --> 00:55:40,963
What? You want me to avoid her?
She's one of my bosses.

945
00:55:41,047 --> 00:55:43,090
Teo, what did we get into?

946
00:55:43,174 --> 00:55:45,843
Weren't you the one who wanted to work
under the Veronas?

947
00:55:46,802 --> 00:55:49,472
Stop getting involved.
You're not only putting Gem in danger

948
00:55:49,555 --> 00:55:51,140
but also yourself, me, my family

949
00:55:51,223 --> 00:55:52,641
and everyone else
who has a connection to me.

950
00:55:52,725 --> 00:55:54,351
And they don't know about our connection.

951
00:55:54,435 --> 00:55:55,895
I already told Ma'am Gem.

952
00:55:55,978 --> 00:55:57,563
Gem won't put us in danger.

953
00:55:57,646 --> 00:56:00,316
That woman? Do you really trust her?

954
00:56:00,399 --> 00:56:01,400
Yes.

955
00:56:03,194 --> 00:56:04,653
Do you still love her?

956
00:56:05,654 --> 00:56:08,532
I already told you, didn't I?
I don't have time for that kind of stuff.

957
00:56:13,913 --> 00:56:16,665
Yes, ma'am.
I'll be there in 20 minutes.

958
00:56:16,749 --> 00:56:17,875
Thank you.

959
00:56:20,377 --> 00:56:22,004
- Ma'am Gem.
- Yes?

960
00:56:22,088 --> 00:56:25,466
Madam is asking
what cut you want from these.

961
00:56:26,383 --> 00:56:28,427
- I'll go with the middle one.
- All right. Thank you, ma'am.

962
00:56:28,511 --> 00:56:29,762
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

963
00:56:29,845 --> 00:56:30,930
Where are you going?

964
00:56:31,847 --> 00:56:34,266
To a client meeting.
Where else would I go?

965
00:56:34,767 --> 00:56:37,436
Cancel it, please.
We're going on a vacation.

966
00:56:37,520 --> 00:56:39,438
All of your bags are packed...
and in the car.

967
00:56:39,522 --> 00:56:42,149
Don't we have a family dinner later?

968
00:56:42,233 --> 00:56:43,526
Let's not tell them.

969
00:56:43,609 --> 00:56:44,985
Mama wouldn't allow it.

970
00:56:45,778 --> 00:56:46,862
We can surprise them.

971
00:56:46,946 --> 00:56:48,823
Anyway, Teo's waiting outside.

972
00:56:48,906 --> 00:56:50,991
And he'll be driving us to Batangas.

973
00:56:53,202 --> 00:56:54,036
Do you remember that resort

974
00:56:54,120 --> 00:56:54,995
you wanted to go to?

975
00:56:56,664 --> 00:56:59,375
We can check it out
and stay there for a few days.

976
00:57:08,676 --> 00:57:09,760
Teo!

977
00:57:11,929 --> 00:57:13,347
What happened?

978
00:57:13,430 --> 00:57:14,807
The engine cut out, sir.

979
00:57:14,890 --> 00:57:16,517
Didn't you check it before we left?

980
00:57:17,059 --> 00:57:18,894
I checked it this morning.

981
00:57:18,978 --> 00:57:20,437
Wait, I'll check it again.

982
00:57:28,070 --> 00:57:29,071
Love.

983
00:57:30,156 --> 00:57:31,782
Why don't you seem excited, love?

984
00:57:33,993 --> 00:57:35,828
I have a lot of pending work.

985
00:57:36,620 --> 00:57:37,830
And with everything that's happening,

986
00:57:37,913 --> 00:57:39,498
how do you expect me to be excited?

987
00:57:39,582 --> 00:57:40,833
I understand.

988
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:43,127
You're still upset with me.

989
00:57:43,961 --> 00:57:45,880
I promise I'll make it
up to you this week.

990
00:57:45,963 --> 00:57:48,591
This trip is gonna be
very memorable for us, love.

991
00:57:52,303 --> 00:57:53,262
Teo!

992
00:57:53,345 --> 00:57:54,889
I'm still checking on it, sir.

993
00:57:57,725 --> 00:57:59,685
- Can we go?
- Wait, ma'am.

994
00:58:10,654 --> 00:58:12,698
Teo? Teo!

995
00:58:22,166 --> 00:58:23,250
Teo!

996
00:58:30,549 --> 00:58:32,927
Hey. Wake up.

997
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:34,595
What happened? Teo!

998
00:58:35,095 --> 00:58:36,764
Wake up! Teo!

999
00:59:33,445 --> 00:59:34,905
<i>It's pretty late, Larajean,</i>

1000
00:59:34,989 --> 00:59:37,032
to visit a co-worker.

1001
00:59:37,116 --> 00:59:39,576
<i>Teo, I can tell if you're lying.</i>

1002
00:59:39,660 --> 00:59:41,412
<i>Why is the judge</i>
<i>particularly suspicious of you?</i>

1003
00:59:41,495 --> 00:59:42,746
Did you have something to do with it?

1004
00:59:42,830 --> 00:59:45,958
Someone suddenly hit my back,
and when I woke up, I was here.

1005
00:59:46,041 --> 00:59:47,293
Then, where is my son?

1006
00:59:47,376 --> 00:59:50,754
<i>Twenty million for your son.</i>
<i>Twenty million for his wife.</i>

1007
00:59:50,838 --> 00:59:53,007
Your priority is my son!

1008
00:59:53,090 --> 00:59:55,217
- <i>What about Ma'am Gem?</i>
- <i>I don't care</i>

1009
00:59:55,301 --> 00:59:57,136
<i>whoever gets left behind.</i>

1010
00:59:57,219 --> 00:59:58,637
They need to escape.

1011
00:59:59,555 --> 01:00:00,431
Gem!
